<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 04 at 1:57AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorm wind gusts will impact portions of Liberty,
Blaine, Hill and Chouteau Counties through 300 AM MDT...
At 156 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 35 miles east of Sunburst to 8 miles southeast
of Chester to near Fort Benton. Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph will move well ahead of their
associated thunderstorms.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Havre, Fort Benton, Chinook, Chester, Big Sandy, Harlem, Parker
School, Beaver Creek, Lothair, Joplin, Hays, Azure, Inverness,
Agency, St. Pierre, Gildford, Sangrey, Boneau, Fort Belknap and
Turner.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
